In 1978 I was &quot;laid off&quot; from a job and told to sign up for<br>
unemployment. When I filled out the paperwork and turned it <br>
in, I joined about forty other people in a waiting area.<br>
In less than 10 minutes, a voice called my name out. &quot;It <br>
says here that you're a Viet Nam veteran. Are you?&quot;<br>
I replied, &quot;Yes&quot;, and was told to step &quot;back here&quot;.<br>
Thirty minutes later, I had a job.<br>
The point being there is a job out there, it may not be the<br>
one you want, but it'll do until a better one comes along.<br>
Don't give up. Keep looking, It is there.<br>
The BEST of wishes for you and your family, Alex.
